                    <comment id="12379526" author="jsdever@sympatico.ca" created="Wed, 24 Jul 2002 05:01:49 +0100"  >HttpClient does support chunking requests and responses on the respective &lt;br/&gt;
output/input streams.  Chunking requests can be set when using the &lt;br/&gt;
HttpConnection method &amp;lt;code&amp;gt;public OutputStream getRequestOutputStream(boolean &lt;br/&gt;
useChunking)&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The PutMethod does allow for chunking with the funky call &lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;code&amp;gt;conn.getRequestOutputStream((isHttp11() &amp;amp;&amp;amp; (null == getRequestHeader&lt;br/&gt;
(&amp;quot;Content-Length&amp;quot;))&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt; and then writes to the output stream.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
But the PostMethod just calls con.write directly, so the chunking code in the &lt;br/&gt;
stream is bypassed.  This seems like a reasonable request to do in the 2.0 &lt;br/&gt;
timeframe.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
                    <comment id="12379527" author="oleg.kalnichevski@bearingpoint.com" created="Sat, 1 Feb 2003 08:14:06 +0000"  >Support for chunk encoded requests in all entity enclosing methods has been&lt;br/&gt;
implemented</comment>
